\begin{align*}
x - 160^{\circ} &= 70^{\circ} + 180^{\circ}k \\
x &= 230^{\circ} + 180^{\circ}k.
\end{align*}
We want the smallest positive integer $x$. For $k = -1$, we get $x = 230^{\circ} - 180^{\circ} = 50^{\circ}$. For $k = -2$, we get $x = 230^{\circ} - 360^{\circ} = -130^{\circ}$, which is not positive.
